[1] ECDC Surveillance Report
Date: Fri 21 Dec 2012
Source: European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) [edited]
http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/press/news/Lists/News/ECDC_DispForm.aspx?List=32e43ee8-e230-4424-a783-85742124029a&ID=815&RootFolder=%2Fen%2Fpress%2Fnews%2FLists%2FNews


The EU [European Union] has returned to similar numbers of measles cases as seen before the large outbreaks of 2010 and 2011.

The new December [2012] Measles and Rubella Monitoring Report by ECDC shows that the total number of measles cases in the EU is 7016 for 2012 compared with some 30 000 for 2011. Individually, 12 of 29 EU/EEA [European Union/European Economic Area] countries had less than one case of measles per million population in the last 12 months, low enough to meet the WHO elimination target set for 2015. However, 5 countries: France, Italy, Romania, Spain, and the United Kingdom accounted for 94 per cent of the reported cases.

