Total / 8795 / 17.3
===================

Conclusion: Romania, Ireland, the United Kingdom, France, Italy, and Spain remain the laggards in measles control.

Latest development -- as of 20 Dec 2012
---------------------------------------
The December 2012 Measles and Rubella Monitoring Report shows that measles cases in the EU are down to the same level as before the large European outbreaks in 2010 and 2011. Individually, 12 of 29 EU/EEA countries met the WHO elimination target of less than one case of measles per million population in the last 12 months.

The 29 contributing EU/ and EEA countries reported 7016 cases of measles from January to October 2012 and 8795 cases during the last 12-month period from November 2011 to October 2012.

