[4] UK (Devon)
Date: Tue 18 Dec 2012
Source: Top News, Arab Emirates [abbreviated & edited]


The Health Protection Agency (HPA) has sent out warnings to parents regarding the measles outbreak and has urged parents to take care of vaccination in their children. The outbreak has sent 3 students of Park Community School in Barnstaple home. The HPA along with NHS [National Health Service] Devon and the school are now sending letters to parents to make sure they are informed of the disease outbreak.

The HPA is now involved in making people informed about this highly infectious disease and the need for vaccination. Symptoms of measles include cold with runny nose, conjunctivitis, fever, aches, and a dry cough. People mainly vulnerable to the disease are children, pregnant women, infants, people with HIV/AIDS, leukemia and other cancers, and organ transplants.

If any such symptoms are found in your child, don't send him or her to school, and keep your child away from other children. In addition, keep them isolated from persons who are most vulnerable to this disease.

[byline: Kanika Mehta]

